The best was kept -- the fir floors, the wide trim, the cast iron door hardware, the original china cupboard from the 1900's. We added a lot of glass block, a second bathroom, a dressing room, a marble floor for the kitchen.

 Our street was built in the street car era, and has come full circle -- the Green Line station at the Capitol is only a couple of blocks away. Or you can walk or bike to downtown -- Charles Avenue is a designated bikeway.

All systems are up to date, including new windows and exterior doors. The interior is designed and painted to please the eye (at least mine).

 We like our street, we even find it amusing. 

 182 Charles has the following:

 1. Downstairs: 

 *Eat in kitchen with abundant cabinets, farm sink, dishwasher, stone island, marble floor, and pantry;
 *Dining room, with large china cabinet for dishes and linens
 *Full bath, with shower big enough for two
 *Large living room
 *Separate laundry room

 2. Upstairs:

 *Front master suite, with bedroom, bedroom closet, separate sitting room/office, and rear, and dressing room with walk in closet and cosmetic sink.
*Rear bedroom, with closet
 *Full bath, with clawfoot tub (for that Saturday morning soak in January)

 There is a large thrust deck out back. There is parking for one car in a shared garage, and another space for a second vehicle outside.

 There are 9 foot ceilings and natural wood floors throughout, with ceramic baths.

 We prefer cat owners, but will take tenants without . . .

 Come join our neighborhood!

Owner pays trash, lawn mowing, and snow removal of front sidewalk and parking areas .  Tenant pays utilities, including water, tends flower beds, and removes snow from entry sidewalk.

description: Recently sold: $289,900. Only one block from Como Lake, this spacious mid-century home offers an open floor plan, main floor family room addition with brand new carpet, vaulted ceilings, wood floors, attached garage and more! Three bedrooms all on upper level w/full bathroom and the basement has been remodeled into a non-conforming studio apartment with kitchenette, 3/4 bath, and separate entrance. Bonus basement hobby room with tons of storage! Newer furnace, air conditioning, and roof will put your mind at ease year-round. With a family room fireplace, spacious deck, and fully fenced backyard, you'll have great entertaining spaces for every season. Finally, the location can't be beat nestled 15 minutes from either downtown Minneapolis or St Paul and walking distance to Como Regional Park. This 450-acre public space features a zoo, lake, golf course, gardens &multiple picnic pavilions. Endless entertainment!

description: Recently sold: $635,000. Beautifully restored turn-of-the-century home - 4(+)bedrooms, 3 full baths, brand new 2nd floor laundry, 3 season porch, fenced in backyard. Immediately out your front door you can walk, bike or rollerblade around beautiful Lake Como (the heart of historic Como Park - one of the top attractions in Minnesota). Or you can simply sit on your front patio and enjoy people-watching in this truly fantastic neighborhood.
